Description: This registry defines the Update Manager messages for Redfish PLDMBundle

FirmwareActivationCompleted.Description: Indicates a firmware activation has completed successfully.

FirmwareActivationFailed.Description: Indicates a firmware activation has failed.

FirmwareActivationStarted.Description: Indicates a firmware activation has started.

FirmwareBackgroundCopyCompleted.Description: Indicates that firmware background copy has completed.
FirmwareBackgroundCopyCompleted.Message: %1 firmware was successfully replicated to backup flash.

FirmwareBackgroundCopyFailed.Description: Indicates that firmware background copy failed.
FirmwareBackgroundCopyFailed.Message: %1 firmware failed being replicated to backup flash.

FirmwareBackgroundCopyStarted.Description: Indicates that firmware background copy has started.
FirmwareBackgroundCopyStarted.Message: %1 firmware is being replicated to backup flash.

FirmwareUpdateCompleted.Description: Indicates a firmware update has completed successfully.
FirmwareUpdateCompleted.Message: %1 firmware update to version %2 completed successfully.

FirmwareUpdateFailed.Description: Indicates a firmware update has failed.

FirmwareUpdateSkippedVersionMatch.Description: Indicates that firmware update was skipped due to a version match.
FirmwareUpdateSkippedVersionMatch.Message: %1 firmware was skipped as version on target is the same (%2).

FirmwareUpdateSkippedVersionOlder.Description: Indicates that firmware update was skipped as firmware on device is newer.
FirmwareUpdateSkippedVersionOlder.Message: %1 firmware was skipped as version on target is newer (%2).

FirmwareUpdateStaged.Description: Indicates a firmware update has staged successfully.
FirmwareUpdateStaged.Message: %1 firmware update to version %2 staged successfully.

FirmwareUpdateStarted.Description: Indicates a firmware update has started.

FirmwareVerificationSuccess.Description: Indicates a firmware verification has succeeded.

FirmwareVersionMismatch.Description: Indicates a firmware Firmware Version Mismatch occurred.

InvalidData.Description: Indicates that server provided invalid data for this resource.
InvalidData.Message: %1 is failed, Server provided invalid data. Please try again after sometime.
InvalidData.Resolution: Retry this request after some time.

InvalidJSON.Description: Indicates that the response body contains invalid JSON.
InvalidJSON.Message: %1 is failed, the response data provided from the server is invalid JSON. Error message is (%2). Invalid JSON is (%3).
InvalidJSON.Resolution: Add properties in the JSON object and resubmit the request.

LibraryFailed.Description: Indicates that fail to load an library.
LibraryFailed.Resolution: Restart the sync-agent and try again.

Timeout.Description: Indicates that the property was not changed or did not cause an error before a timeout occurred.
Timeout.Message: The timeout duration (%1s) was exceeded before the operation on %2 responded.
Timeout.Resolution: Resource is taking more than the configured timeout seconds to respond. Please resubmit the request if necessary.

UpdateManagerError.Description: Indicates that server not able to get data for this resource.
UpdateManagerError.Message: %1 is failed, Server not able to get data for this resource. Please try again after sometime.
UpdateManagerError.Resolution: Retry this request after some time.

Name: Update Manager Message Registry
